value.0: Let me see... perhaps it is best if I ask you a question first. You are a person of great skill, are you not?
I think not. Judging a person's skill and power is an important aspect of my job. Regardless, it is not yet time for us to meet, so this is goodbye.
But... it is not our time to meet yet. So I must bid you farewell.
Hail, friend. You were instrumental in ridding Neverwinter of the Wailing Death, I understand. Allow me to congratulate you on a job well done.
You have shown yourself to be possessed of remarkable courage and resourcefulness. That is fortuitous, for both these qualities will be needed if you are to complete your mission.
But that is not how we should begin. I am known as Aarin Gend, and I have served our Lord Nasher for some time. Hopefully I may be of similar use to you now.
So impatient to get on with business? You are obviously in need of action, and are a courageous warrior. Only one such person is needed to change the world.
Indeed. I already know who you are. There are many who whisper your name right now, and it is my business to listen to them all.
My place lies in the shadows. I have many eyes and ears throughout the northern lands and Neverwinter, and it is my place to inform Lord Nasher where the vipers lay in wait.
I am sure Lord Nasher has informed you to meet with me, so let us cut to the chase. Our main priority is saving Neverwinter from the forces of Luskan.

To that end, we must eliminate the powers that be in Luskan. The city itself is ruled by five pirate lords known as High Captains. Based on a reconaissance report, they are also in charge of the Luskan army.
Eliminating all of the High Captains should send their forces into disarray and perhaps put a stop to the onslaught.
I do hope that you reconsider your decision, friend. Neverwinter does not stand a chance against an army after the impact of the Wailing Death. I will be here.
Ah, always the soldier of fortune. Trust that your reward will be great indeed. Allow me to continue, and I will explain our next steps.
Your determination itself may be all that is needed. Allow me to continue, and I will explain our next steps.
A former pirate, High Captain Taerl is known as one of the first High Captains of Luskan. My intel indicates that he is an experienced adventurer and weaponmaster, so be wary.
One of the oldest of the High Captains, Baram is still a dangerous fighter and he has even more dangerous associates.
High Captain Kurth was a former friend of our Lord Nasher before they became bitter enemies. Watch your back around him, as he is quite the brutish fighter.
Next on the list is High Captain Suljack. A sneaky fellow and master assassin. His tower is likely also filled with traps.
Finally, we have High Captain Rethnor. He has a son named Kensidan, but not much is known about him, besides being nicknamed "The Crow". Be wary of this father and son duo.
They should all be located in their towers in Luskan. Getting into Luskan is another story. As you may already see, the city is under lockdown and entry is impossible.

Luckily for us, there exists another path into the city. There is an entrance to an abandoned mining operation that should bring you into the sewers of Luskan, which should be able to get you into the city proper.
That said, the mines are abandoned for a reason - they have been overrun by a population of umber hulks. What few scouts I have sent have yet to return.
Once you are inside the city, you are not out of the woods yet. I have heard reports that the city itself is under strict surveillance.
According to one such report, the Arcane Brotherhood casted an attunement spell that affected every single person within the city.
As no one is allowed in, they can easily tell if there are intruders in the city. There are wardens that patrol on patrol can easily snuff you out.
If you do manage to get inside the city, exercise caution and stay away from them, or you will be overwhelmed by the entire Luskan military.
Should you manage that, liquidate the High Captains and return to me for further orders. I wish you luck, my friend.
You are back, <FirstName>. Have you something to report?
Then I wish you luck on your mission, my friend.
We must save Neverwinter. To do that, we must stop the oncoming war from Luskan.

To that end, we must eliminate the powers that be in Luskan. The city itself is ruled by five pirate lords known as High Captains. Based on a reconaissance report, they are also in charge of the Luskan army. I will tell you about these High Captains.
No, you are surely mistaken.
Yes, I am.
Yes, yes, let's just get on with it.
Pleased to meet you. My name is <FullName>.
How, exactly, can you help me?
Sorry, that's too much work for me.
Let me think about this, first.
How would I even get into Luskan?
Alright, but the gold better be worth it.
Of course. I will do anything to save Neverwinter.
Thanks. I'll need it.
Nothing yet. Farewell.
Tell me what needs to be done, again.
